are in china. talking about air pollution has become a part of life for both locals and expatriates. even the countryside, depending on the province in question, is not immune. places at higher altitudes or plains like parts of yunnan and sichuan, xinjiang, inner mongolia, tibet and outlying islands such as hainan usually have good air quality. visitors should be prepared to see smog, which can be quite heavy, in nearly all large cities, including those on the coast. you will also hear a lot of noise. construction and renovation are full-time activities. chinese and long-time residents' ears are trained 